Jakadan Amurka ya zargi kasar Sin da "tashin hankali" da "tallan talla"
Wata mako bayan wani jaridar kasar Sin ta wallafa wani sanarwa mai shafuka hudu a wata jaridar Amurka, inda aka yaba wa amfanin cinikin Amurka da China, jakadan Amurka a China ya zargi Beijing da amfani da manema labarai na Amurka wajen yada labaran.
Shugaban Amurka Donald Trump ya yi nuni da wani shafi na biyan kuɗi na China Daily a cikin Des Moines Register, jaridar da ta fi sayarwa a Iowa, bayan ya zargi China da tsoma baki a zaben Amurka na 6 ga Nuwamba, zargin da China ta musanta.
Sanarwar da Trump ya yi cewa Beijing na kokarin tsoma baki a zaben Amurka, ta nuna, a cewar jami'an Amurka da Reuters ta ruwaito, wani sabon mataki ne a wani gagarumin yunkuri na Washington na matsa lamba a kasar Sin.
Ko da yake yana da kyau gwamnatocin ƙasashen waje su saka tallace-tallace don inganta kasuwanci, Beijing da Washington suna cikin faɗaɗa yaƙin kasuwanci a halin yanzu, inda suka ɗora wa juna ƙarin harajin shigo da kaya.
Kudaden da kasar Sin ta biya a farkon yakin cinikayya sun kasance na musamman ne don shafar masu fitar da kaya a jihohi kamar Iowa, wadanda ke goyon bayan Jam'iyyar Republican ta Trump, kamar yadda masana na kasar Sin da Amurka suka ce.
Terry Branstad, jakadan Amurka a kasar Sin kuma tsohon gwamnan Iowa, babban mai fitar da kayayyakin gona zuwa kasar Sin, ya ce kasar Sin ta yi wa ma'aikatan Amurka, manoma da kuma kamfanoni barazana.
"Kasar Sin", kamar yadda Branstad ya rubuta a wani rahoto a cikin jaridar Des Moines Register a ranar Lahadi, "yanzu tana ninka barazanar ta hanyar wallafa tallace-tallace na propaganda a cikin jaridarmu ta kyauta".
Branstad ya rubuta: "Ta wajen yada wannan labaran, gwamnatin kasar Sin tana amfani da 'yancin faɗar albarkacin baki da kuma 'yancin' yan jarida, al'adar da aka daɗe ana yi a Amirka ta wajen saka tallace-tallace a cikin Des Moines Register".
Ya rubuta: "A akasin haka, za ka ga kuri'u masu banbanci a wani kiosk a tsakiyar birnin Beijing, kuma ba za ka ga ainihin yadda ra'ayoyin da jama'ar Sin suke da shi game da matsalar tattalin arziki ba, domin 'yan jarida suna ƙarƙashin ikon jam'iyyar kwaminis ta kasar Sin".
Ya kara da cewa "daya daga cikin manyan jaridu a kasar Sin ya ki wallafa labarinsa", kamar bai san wane jarida ne ya wallafa ba.
